2Scale-dependent propagation of neural emittance. KMS-derived emittance profiles illustrate how information flow from a source neuron reorganizes across inverse temperature regimes (
β
). At high inverse temperature (
↑ β
), communication is localized and dominated by direct synaptic connections. As
β
decreases, multi-step pathways increasingly contribute, producing distributed connectivity patterns. Near the critical regime (
≈ β
β c
), information flow becomes maximally dispersed across the network. Node size reflects distance from the source, and edge coloring distinguishes active from inactive communication pathways. This scale dependence underlies the construction of the structure-informed functional connectome.

